## 📄 Week 3 Summary (NumPy & Pandas)
In Week 3, I learned how to work with data using NumPy and Pandas,which are essential libraries for data analysis in Python. I understood how NumPy arrays allow fast and efficient numerical computations, and how operations like element-wise calculations and array transformations can be performed easily.
Using Pandas, I worked with structured data in the form of DataFrames and Series. I learned how to create datasets, access specific columns, and perform operations like filtering and aggregation. One of the key concepts I learned was handling missing data, where I used methods like filling missing values with the mean to maintain data consistency.
I also performed basic statistical analysis such as calculating average, maximum, and minimum values. Additionally, I used grouping techniques to categorize data and analyze it based on specific conditions. This helped in understanding patterns within the dataset.
The integration of NumPy with Pandas helped me perform numerical operations more efficiently. I also learned how to save processed data into a new file for future use.
Overall, this week provided practical experience in cleaning, analyzing, and transforming data. It strengthened my understanding of real-world data processing and prepared me for further tasks in data visualization and machine learning.
